      "url": "http://www.dominionenergy.com/en/Virginia/Rates-and-Tariffs/Competitive-Energy-Suppliers/Downloadable-Profiles",
      "title": "Downloadable Profiles | Virginia - Dominion Energy",
      "text": "Downloadable Profiles | Virginia | Dominion Energy\n\nSearch Close\n\nVirginia/ Rates and Tariffs/ Competitive Energy Suppliers\n\n# Downloadable Profiles\n\nThe generic load profiles for each customer class are provided in .csv files that can be easily downloaded to a personal computer for further analysis. Each file represents a separate annual profile for a specific customer segment. When using any of the Historic Profiles provided below, you may use the data as presented, or you may choose to either weather normalize it using your own software, or to exclude the demand data from all or part of that time frame.\n\nThe profile for any customer with an interval data recorder, as required for billing, is developed from their specific customer load pattern. Only when a customer does not have any historical usage will they receive a generic profile as determined by the annual load research class studies. In this case, the assigned generic rate class profile is scaled to reflect the customer's actual usage as meters are read. Once the customer accumulates sufficient usage, its load profile will be used in forecasting and preliminary settlement. The customer's actual metered usage will always be used for final settlement.\n\nIt should be noted that non-jurisdictional and Commonwealth of Virginia tariffs are not provided due to their confidential nature.\n\nHow to Download and Save a File\n\n- Select the file you want below and Right Click.\n- This will bring up a sub-menu.\n- Select \"Save Target As\".\n- You should see a \"File Download\" dialog box followed by a \"Save As\" box.\n- The profile name will appear in the \"Save As\" box.\n- Select the folder in which you want to save the file.\n- Click on the \"Save\" button.\n\n## Julian Look Up and Deemed Profiles Overview\n\nLighting Profile This deemed profile assumes about 4,000 hours annual lighting use for residential watch lights and street light customers. This profile is applied as a Julian date profile as the hours of darkness increase through the fall and the winter then decrease in the Spring/ summer. The profile consists of “0” when lights are deemed “off” and “1” when lights are deemed to be “on.” To develop a leap-year version of this file simply repeat the on/off pattern for February 28 for February 29.\n\nFLATONE Profile This deemed profile is used for loads that are considered to be regularly “on” all of the time, such as traffic control. This profile consists of all “1” for every hour. To develop a leap-year version of this file simply repeat the final row to create a 366th observation.\n\nFLATZERO Profile This deemed profile is used for loads that are forecast to be regularly “off” all (or nearly all) of the time, such as curtailable load and standby generation. This profile consists of all “0” for every hour. To develop a leap-year version of this file simply repeat the final row to create a 366th observation.\n\n## Virginia Profiles\n\n#### Dominion Energy Virginia - Residential Rates and Tariffs\n\nResidential - Virginia \" RESVA\"\n\nThis profile is applicable to the following bundled and unbundled Residential rate schedules:\n\n- Schedule 1/1U - Basic Residential Rate\n- Schedule 1P/1PU - TOU\n- Schedule 1S/1SU - Demand TOU\n- Schedule 1T/1TU - Energy TOU\n- Schedule 1W/1WU - Time-Controlled Storage Water Heating\n\nOutdoor Lighting - \" LIGHTING\"\n\nThis profile is applicable to the following bundled and unbundled Residential rate schedules:\n\n- Schedule 27/27U - Outdoor Lighting-HPSV\n- Schedule 28/28U - Outdoor Lighting-non HPSV\n- Schedule 29/29U - Privately Owned Outdoor Lighting\n\n#### Dominion Energy Virginia - Business Rates and Tariffs\n\nChurch and Synagogue Service - \" chu\"\n\nThis profile is applicable to the following bundled and unbundled Business rate schedules:\n\n- Schedule 5C/5CU - Church and Synagogue Service\n- Schedule 5P/5PU - TOU Church Rate\n\nSmall General Service - \" GS1\"\n\nThis profile is applicable to the following bundled and unbundled Business rate schedules:\n\n- Schedule GS-1/GS-1U Small General Service (under 30 kW)\n- Schedule 7/7U Electric Heating\n\nIntermediate General Service - \" GS2\"\n\nThis profile is applicable to the following bundled and unbundled Business rate schedules:\n\n- Schedule GS-2/GS-2U Intermediate General Service\n- Schedule GS-2T/GS-2TU TOU Intermediate General Service\n\nLarge General Service Secondary Voltage - \" GS3\"\n\nThis profile is applicable to the following bundled and unbundled Business rate schedules. Accounts on this rate schedule will have an interval data recorder. An account without sufficient historical usage will be assigned to this generic profile until sufficient usage is available to generate a distinct load profile.\n\n- Schedule GS-3/GS-3U Large General Service\n\nLarge General Service Primary Voltage - \" GS4\"\n\nThis profile is applicable to the following bundled and unbundled Business rate schedules. Accounts on this rate schedule will have an interval data recorder. An account without sufficient historical usage will be assigned to this generic profile until sufficient usage is available to generate a distinct load profile.\n\n- Schedule GS-4/GS-4U Large General Service Primary Voltage\n\nOTHER\n\nCustomers served on the following sparsely populated rate schedules are profiled using the most appropriate business profile (GS-1, GS-2, GS-3 or GS-4) as determined by the demand requirement of the GS schedules' applicability provisions and the individual customer's usage history. Some customers on these rates will be metered with a billing interval data recorder and are only profiled until sufficient history is available to generate a distinct load profile:\n\n- Schedule 5/5U - Small General Service\n- Schedule 6/6U Large General Service\n- Schedule 6TS/6TSU - Thermal Storage Schedule RTP Real Time Pricing\n- Schedule 10/10U - Large General Service\n\nOutdoor Lighting - \" LIGHTING\"\n\nThis profile is applicable t