      "text": "Business Rates | Virginia | Dominion Energy\n\nSearch Close\n\nVirginia/ Rates and Tariffs\n\n# Business Rates\n\nRate Schedules serve Virginia customers who purchase both the supply (generation and transmission) and delivery (distribution) portions of their electric service from Dominion Energy Virginia. Customers that wish to participate in Retail Access will do so under Virginia Jurisdictional Rate Schedules 1, GS-1, GS-2, GS-3, GS-3EV, GS-4, 5C, 24, 27, or 28.\n\n(This is the entire filed tariff document as filed with the Virginia State Corporation Commission. Separate documents for each rate schedule are provided below.)\n\nDominion Energy Virginia collects and remits a consumption tax for all consumed kWh delivered and billed by the company. Consumption tax information and associated rates are located at the end of the filed tariff.\n\n## Rate Schedules\n\n#### Rates\n\n- Schedule 5 - Small General Service (Closed)\n- Schedule 5C - Church and Synagogue Service\n- Schedule 5P - TOU Church Rate\n- Schedule GS 1 - Small General Service (under 30 kW)\n- Schedule DP-1 - Small General Service (Experimental)\n- Schedule GS-2 - Intermediate General Service (30-500 kW)\n- Schedule GS-2T - TOU Intermediate General Service\n- Schedule DP-2 - Intermediate General Service (Experimental)\n- Schedule GS-3 - Large General Service Secondary Voltage\n- Schedule GS-3EV - Public Charging (Experimental)\n- Schedule GS-4 - Large General Service Primary Voltage\n- Market-Based Rate Schedule\n- Schedule 6 - Large General Service (Closed)\n- Schedule 7 - Electric Heating (Closed)\n- Schedule 8 - Supplementary, Maintenance, Standby Service\n\n#### Riders\n\n- Exhibit of Applicable Riders\n- Rider A - Fuel Charge Rider\n- Rider C1A - Peak-Shaving Increment Rider\n- Rider C4A - Energy Efficiency Increment Rider\n- Rider CCR - Coal Ash Closure\n- Rider CE - Clean Energy Projects and Power Purchase Agreements\n- Rider CERC - Chesterfield Energy Reliability Center\n- Rider CRC - Manufacturing and Commercial Competitiveness Retention Credit Rider\n- Rider D - Tax Effect Recovery\n- Rider DIST - Distribution Facilities Projects\n- Rider E - Environmental Projects\n- Rider EDR - Economic Development\n- Rider F - Receivers or Trustees\n- Rider G - Renewable Energy Program(Effective 4/1/2025)\n- Rider G - Renewable Energy Program(Effective 7/1/2026)\n- Rider GEN - Generation Facilities Projects\n- Rider OSW - Coastal Virginia Offshore Wind\n- Rider PIPP - Universal Service Fee\n- Rider RBB - Rural Broadband Pilot Projects\n- Rider REC - Renewable Energy Certificate Purchase Program\n- Rider RGGI - Regional Greenhouse Gas Initiative\n- Rider RPS - Renewable Energy Portfolio Standard\n- Rider SMR - Small Modular Reactor\n- Rider SNA - Surry and North Anna Nuclear Life Extension Program\n- Rider T1 - Transmission\n- Rider TRG - 100 Percent Total Renewable Generation\n- Rider VCS - Virginia Community Solar Pilot Program(Effective 4/1/2025)\n- Rider VCS - Virginia Community Solar Pilot Program(Effective 6/1/2026)\n\n#### Special Tariffs\n\n- Schedule 6TS - Thermal Storage\n- Schedule 10 - Large General Service\n- Schedule 19 - Cogeneration & Small Power Producers\n- Schedule SP - Solar Purchase (Experimental)\n- Schedule SS - Shared Solar\n- Schedule 24 - Solid State Outdoor Lighting\n- Schedule 25 - Privately Owned Outdoor Lighting (Night Only)\n- Schedule 27 - Outdoor Lighting (HPSV)\n- Schedule 28 - Outdoor Lighting (non-HPSV)\n- Schedule 29 - Privately Owned Outdoor Lighting\n- Schedule CFG - Carbon-Free or Renewable Generation Supply Service (Experimental)\n- Schedule EVCF - Electric Vehicle Charging Fleet Service\n- Schedule EVCL2 - Electric Vehicle Level 2 Charging Service\n- Schedule EVFCP - Electric Vehicle Direct Current Fast Charging Pricing Tariff\n- Schedule EVL2P - Electric Vehicle Level Two Pricing Tariff\n- Schedule RF - Environmental Attributes Purchase from Renewable Energy Facilities (Experimental)\n\n#### Deferred Fuel Tariffs